fields.summary: AI/ML: Explore Solutions to Handle Token Rate Limits in Jira Issue Summary Generator

issuetype.description: A task that needs to be done.
issuetype.name: Task

fields.description:
*Summary:*
While generating Jira issue summaries using LLM in LangChain, issues arise when processing large sprints:
 # {*}Skipping Tickets Issue{*}: For sprints with more than 40 tickets (approx) , some tickets are missing from the generated summary.
 # {*}Rate Limit Exceeded Error{*}: For sprints with more than 80 tickets (approx) , the following error occurs:

{code:java}
Error code: 429 - {'error': {'code': '429', 'message': 'Requests to the ChatCompletions_Create Operation under Azure OpenAI API version 2024-08-01-preview have exceeded token rate limit of your current OpenAI S0 pricing tier. Please retry after 86400 seconds. Please go here: https://aka.ms/oai/quotaincrease if you would like to further increase the default rate limit.'}}{code}
This ticket aims to explore different solutions to resolve the above issues while generating the summary.

resolution.description: A fix for this issue is checked into the tree and tested.
resolution.name: Fixed

worklogs.comment: Explored solutions to avoid token limit reached error for large sprint.
1. Explored different techniques to avoid rate limit error including truncation, chunking, summarization, Removing redundant items, caching, Backoff Strategy, and FallBack Strategy.

1. Explored techniques using LLM to generate summaries for a large number of issues concurrently.
2. Compared the LLM's summary generation time for a sprint with a large number of issues, both with and without chunking, and tested various chunk sizes.

1. Explored different techniques for handling rate limit errors.  
2. Wrote code to reduce Jira issue content using PEGASUS, NLTK, and regex, and observed the performance and output.

End-to-end development services (design, development, deployment).

Offers AI-powered assistance to guide the user through the app-building process.

Less community support hard to find how to integrate UI and API,
